			<h1>Road Cycle</h1>
			 <p>A road cycle, also known as a road bike, is designed for smooth, paved surfaces and built for speed and efficiency. 
			 It features lightweight frames, narrow tires, and drop handlebars to enhance aerodynamics and comfort during long rides. 
			 Road bikes are ideal for racing, commuting, and fitness, offering a fast and smooth ride on highways and city streets.
			  The gear system allows for easy shifting, making it adaptable to different terrains. Popular among cycling enthusiasts, road bikes are known for their performance and endurance over long distances.</p>
			</div>
