			<h1 id=h3>Hybrid Cycle</h1>
			<p id=p1>
A hybrid cycle combines features of road bikes and mountain bikes, making it versatile for a variety of terrains. 
It typically has a comfortable, upright riding position, wider tires for stability, and a sturdy frame. Hybrid bikes are ideal for commuting, recreational riding, and light off-road use.
 They offer a smooth ride on both paved roads and unpaved trails. 
With their practical design, hybrid bikes are perfect for cyclists seeking comfort, durability, and performance in different environments.</p>
